# Project Structure

This is a Flutter monorepo managed by Melos.

## Main Areas

- `apps/multichoice` is the main Flutter app.
- `apps/showcase` is a showcase app and is ignored by Melos.
- `packages/core` owns application state, services, repositories, controllers, wrappers, exceptions, and utilities.
- `packages/models` owns DTOs, database models, API models, enums, and mappers.
- `packages/theme` owns shared theme extensions and app colors.
- `packages/ui_kit` owns reusable widgets, dialogs, loaders, scroll behavior, and UI constants.
- `functions`, `docs`, and `designs` are separate support areas.

## Boundaries

- App UI belongs in `apps/multichoice/lib/presentation`, `layouts`, `app`, or `utils` following nearby structure.
- Shared business logic belongs in `packages/core`, not directly in the app presentation layer.
- Shared models belong in `packages/models`; do not duplicate model shapes in app code.
- Reusable styling and widgets belong in `packages/theme` or `packages/ui_kit`.
- Use `export.dart` barrel files where the package or folder already uses them.

## Required Patterns

- Services, wrappers, controllers, and repositories use `interfaces/` and `implementations/` or existing repository `interfaces/` and `implementation/` folders.
- UI constants live in `packages/ui_kit/lib/src/constants`.
- Tests mirror the source structure and use existing mocks when available.

